On june 12, 2012
[68111]

Rules are:

1) Only armies with SIX or fewer troopers allowed. Any army that gets a 7th trooper will be removed from the listing

2) To sign up add a link to your HQ page (tinyurl is allowed to help with forum formatting issues) and army name then playername afterwards. This is to make it as easy as possible for everyone else to see which army name to use to fight.
e.g. http://tinyurl.com/knife-fighters Knife Fighters / pickupsticks
LINK then ARMY NAME then / PLAYER NAME

3) To move up the ranking, beat the person above you then post a link to the replay here. Copy and paste the list, adjusting your position, and re-post it.

4) MAKE SURE you use the correct list from the last post in the thread. MAKE SURE nobody else has posted at the same time as you. If this happens, then edit your post to correct it. Anyone that messes up the list more than three times in a month will be penalized five places, because it's a real pain for everyone else.

5) Only fights where you sent the challenge (are on the left) are allowed. Only direct challenge fights are allowed. Fights that end in BAT1/BAT2/BAT3 or MISS1/MISS2/MISS3 are not eligible.

6) A player may choose to go "inactive" by marking their army with [REST]
e.g. [REST] http://tinyurl.com/knife-fighters Knife Fighters / pickupsticks
If a player directly above you is inactive and you can beat the next player then you may skip the inactive player.
e.g.1) player A
2) [REST] player B
3) player CPlayer C may choose to move up into first place if they can beat player A. They cannot move into 2nd place unless they beat player B in the usual way.

7) Only one army per player is allowed.

...that should be enough rules to keep things in order, but we all know how it works so stop reading and get fighting.

pickupsticks
45424Is my army underleveled?

Well, you are at a disadvantage of several level points when facing M-Inc. They're currently (10 - 10 - 9 - 9 - 9) eight points ahead of you for power. For smaller armies this can make more of a difference than when comparing larger armies. A couple of show-stopper upgrades for your guys could easily see you wiping the floor with them, even though they're rated higher than you, so keep your fingers crossed for something decent in the shop next time around.

I like that this gives the chance for new players with smaller armies to fight armies on their level at the same time as giving them a goal to reach without getting completely discouraged by the armies that exist since the beginning of the game (English server, anyways ^^).


Anyways I'd like to thank X-Drake for creating this topic .
It was a great idea in my opinion

[344756]

Thanks for the suggestion I've thought about it before but landed on one major reason for why it wouldn't work well for my army at the moment. Against armies of 6, only one spy can come out and that would be the spy that is placed higher up in the order you put your spies in. So currently my army's formation is this: http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/... Ken is placed above Ryu in deployment order so that he gets priority over him in deploying at the opponents end. Putting Ryu in Ken's place would mean that Ryu will be the one guaranteed to come out in the opponents side rather than Ken whose a better spy.


Ken is indeed the better spy compared to Ryu(I have spies of my own, I should know). but against sabotage-heavy armies(Like Wolf's Raiders for example), he usually get sabotaged completely. Weaponless spies can only hope for friendly fire or fists kills. Putting Ryu in first gives you a better chance for a spy to cause damage at the enemy lines when against heavy sabotage, since he has more weapons then Ken. It's something you should consider when against saboteur heavy armies. I'm sure you'll do fine either way.

Just my two cents, of course.
Saboteurless armies, like Nightblade for example, you should use Ken. No doubt about that one.
